
<div class="book_part" id="CH_INDEX"><div id="CH_2_SEC001" style="text-align:left;" class="level1"><a name="CH_2_SEC001" id="CH_2_SEC001"></a><h2>CAFETERIA PLANS</h2><p class="indent2">* Automatic enrollment</p><p class="indent3">- Deemed &#167;125 compensation for employees who do not have option to elect out of automatic enrollment health plan, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_1A/CH_1A_SEC418#CH_1A_SEC418" target="_blank">1A.101</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Plan amendment required to include deemed &#167;125 compensation, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_1A/CH_1A_SEC420#CH_1A_SEC420" target="_blank">1A.102</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Definition of a cafeteria plan, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_1A/CH_1A_SEC259#CH_1A_SEC259" target="_blank">1A.52</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Must be a choice between cash and non-taxable benefits in order for there to be a cafeteria plan, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_1A/CH_1A_SEC259#CH_1A_SEC259" target="_blank">1A.52</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Reporting requirements for cafeteria plans,</p><p class="">see <b><a href="/browse-index/2014-erisa-outline-book/B001?indexKey=f#CH_3_SEC18">FORM 5500</a></b></p><p class=""><b>CANADIAN RETIREMENT PLANS, see NONRESIDENT ALIENS</b></p></div><div id="CH_2_SEC001" style="text-align:left;" class="level1"><a name="CH_2_SEC001" id="CH_2_SEC001"></a><h2>CAPITAL GAINS</h2><p class="indent2">* Election for certain lump sum distributions,</p><p class="">see <b>LUMP SUM DISTRIBUTIONS</b></p><p class="indent2">* Employer securities distributed from plan: sale of distributed securities,</p><p class="">see <b>EMPLOYER SECURITIES</b></p><p class=""><b>CASH BALANCE PLANS/ STATUTORY HYBRID PLANS</b></p><p class="indent2">* Accruals under cash balance plans,</p><p class="">see <b>ACCRUAL OF BENEFITS</b></p><p class="indent2">* Age discrimination for cash balance and other hybrid plans, see <b>AGE DISCRIMINATION</b></p><p class="indent2">* Definition of cash balance plan, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_1A/CH_1A_SEC261#CH_1A_SEC261" target="_blank">1A.52</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Hypothetical account balance may be treated as present value of vested benefit for distributions made after August 17, 2006 (safe-harbor present value rule), <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_6/CH_6_SEC181#CH_6_SEC181" target="_blank">6.66</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Additional rules for applying safe-harbor present value rule, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_6/CH_6_SEC189#CH_6_SEC189" target="_blank">6.70</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Market rate of return rules, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_3B/CH_3B_SEC1373#CH_3B_SEC1373" target="_blank">3B.482</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Statutory hybrid plan/statutory hybrid plan formula/accumulated benefit/lump-sum-based benefit formula definition, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_3B/CH_3B_SEC1362#CH_3B_SEC1362" target="_blank">3B.476</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Whipsaw issue eliminated by PPA 2006, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_6/CH_6_SEC178#CH_6_SEC178" target="_blank">6.65</a></b></p><p class=""><b>CASH OR DEFERRED ARRANGEMENTS, see SECTION 401(k) PLANS</b></p><p class=""><b>CASH-OUT DISTRIBUTIONS, see VESTING RULES</b></p><p class=""><b>CATCH-UP CONTRIBUTIONS</b></p><p class="indent2">* Administrative issues for plans that permit catch-up contributions, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_11/CH_11_SEC835#CH_11_SEC835" target="_blank">11.290</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* ADP test: treatment of catch-up contributions,</p><p class="">see <b>ADP AND ACP TESTING</b></p><p class="indent2">* Aggregation of plans to determine whether catch-up limit is exceeded, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_11/CH_11_SEC974#CH_11_SEC974" target="_blank">11.333</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Annual catch-up contribution limit, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_11/CH_11_SEC791#CH_11_SEC791" target="_blank">11.272</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Calendar year determination, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_11/CH_11_SEC871#CH_11_SEC871" target="_blank">11.303</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Consequences of exceeding the annual limit, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_11/CH_11_SEC830#CH_11_SEC830" target="_blank">11.289</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- May not exceed compensation, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_11/CH_11_SEC796#CH_11_SEC796" target="_blank">11.274</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Table of dollar limits, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_17/CH_17_SEC031#CH_17_SEC031" target="_blank">17.39</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Calendar year limit on catch-up contributions, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_11/CH_11_SEC871#CH_11_SEC871" target="_blank">11.303</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Coverage testing: treatment of catch-up contributions,</p><p class="">see <b>COVERAGE TESTING</b></p><p class="indent2">* Definition of catch-up contributions, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_1A/CH_1A_SEC297#CH_1A_SEC297" target="_blank">1A.65</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Designated Roth contributions may be catch-up contributions, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_11/CH_11_SEC1818#CH_11_SEC1818" target="_blank">11.678</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* IRAs: catch-up contribution option for IRA owners over age 50,</p><p class="">see <b>IRAs</b></p><p class="indent2">* Lost opportunity to make catch-up contributions: EPCRS correction method, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_15/CH_15_SEC785#CH_15_SEC785" target="_blank">15.676</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Matching contributions may be made on catch-up contributions, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_11/CH_11_SEC849#CH_11_SEC849" target="_blank">11.294</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Noncalendar plan year: how catch-up limit is administered, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_11/CH_11_SEC872#CH_11_SEC872" target="_blank">11.303</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Nondiscrimination testing issues relating to catch-up contributions,</p><p class="">see <b>NONDISCRIMINATION TESTING</b></p><p class="indent2">* Other limit must be exceeded before elective deferrals are treated as catch-up contributions, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_11/CH_11_SEC805#CH_11_SEC805" target="_blank">11.276</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Plan imposed limits, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_11/CH_11_SEC810#CH_11_SEC810" target="_blank">11.279</a></b></p><p class="indent4">&#9670; Must be set forth in document or authorized by document to be set under administrative procedures, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_11/CH_11_SEC811#CH_11_SEC811" target="_blank">11.279</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Statutory limits, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_11/CH_11_SEC806#CH_11_SEC806" target="_blank">11.277</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Plan document language needed to authorize catch-up contributions, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_11/CH_11_SEC862#CH_11_SEC862" target="_blank">11.300</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Plan-imposed limit on elective deferrals</p><p class="indent3">- Does not apply to catch-up contributions, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_3A/CH_3A_SEC182#CH_3A_SEC182" target="_blank">3A.72</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Treatment as excess allocation under EPCRS procedure, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_15/CH_15_SEC564#CH_15_SEC564" target="_blank">15.562</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* SARSEPs may permit catch-up contributions, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_11/CH_11_SEC847#CH_11_SEC847" target="_blank">11.294</a></b>, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_12/CH_12_SEC039#CH_12_SEC039" target="_blank">12.9</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Section 403(b) plans may permit catch-up contributions, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_16/CH_16_SEC263#CH_16_SEC263" target="_blank">16.57</a></b>, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_11/CH_11_SEC790#CH_11_SEC790" target="_blank">11.272</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Separate accounting of catch-up contributions apart from other elective deferrals not necessary, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_11/CH_11_SEC848#CH_11_SEC848" target="_blank">11.294</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* SIMPLE-401(k) plans may permit catch-up contributions, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_11/CH_11_SEC846#CH_11_SEC846" target="_blank">11.293</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Top heavy rules: application to catch-up contributions,</p><p class="">see <b>TOP HEAVY RULES</b></p><p class="indent2">* Types of plans that may permit catch-up contributions, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_11/CH_11_SEC790#CH_11_SEC790" target="_blank">11.272</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Universal availability requirement,</p><p class="">see <b>NONDISCRIMINATION TESTING</b></p><p class="indent2">* Who is eligible to make catch-up contributions? <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_11/CH_11_SEC800#CH_11_SEC800" target="_blank">11.275</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Age 50 requirement, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_11/CH_11_SEC801#CH_11_SEC801" target="_blank">11.275</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Death before 50th birthday, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_11/CH_11_SEC804#CH_11_SEC804" target="_blank">11.276</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Termination of employment before 50th birthday, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_11/CH_11_SEC803#CH_11_SEC803" target="_blank">11.276</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Treated as 50 for entire calendar year if 50th birthday occurs in that year, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_11/CH_11_SEC801#CH_11_SEC801" target="_blank">11.275</a></b></p></div><div id="CH_2_SEC001" style="text-align:left;" class="level1"><a name="CH_2_SEC001" id="CH_2_SEC001"></a><h2>CHANGE IN FORM OF ENTITY</h2><p class="indent2">* Unincorporated business incorporates or vice versa</p><p class="indent3">- Effect on benefit accrual, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_3B/CH_3B_SEC102#CH_3B_SEC102" target="_blank">3B.41</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Effect on earned income calculation, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_1A/CH_1A_SEC716#CH_1A_SEC716" target="_blank">1A.186</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Effect on employer deduction calculation, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_7/CH_7_SEC2078#CH_7_SEC2078" target="_blank">7.673</a></b></p><p class=""><b>CHARITABLE DEDUCTIONS, see ESTATE AND GIFT TAXES</b></p><p class=""><b>CHARITABLE REMAINDER UNITRUST (CRUT), see ESTATE AND GIFT TAXES</b></p></div><div id="CH_2_SEC001" style="text-align:left;" class="level1"><a name="CH_2_SEC001" id="CH_2_SEC001"></a><h2>CHECKLISTS</h2><p class="indent2">* ADP and ACP testing issues</p><p class="indent3">- 2012 plan years, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_11/CH_11_SEC1877#CH_11_SEC1877" target="_blank">11.711</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- 2013 plan years, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_11/CH_11_SEC1877#CH_11_SEC1877" target="_blank">11.762</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Audit issues, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_15/CH_15_SEC923#CH_15_SEC923" target="_blank">15.721</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Classifications of different types of plans, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_15/CH_15_SEC163#CH_15_SEC163" target="_blank">15.253</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Compensation definitions, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_15/CH_15_SEC279#CH_15_SEC279" target="_blank">15.361</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Coverage and nondiscrimination testing, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_15/CH_15_SEC335#CH_15_SEC335" target="_blank">15.486</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Determination letter procedures, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_15/CH_15_SEC141#CH_15_SEC141" target="_blank">15.229</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Employer responsibilities relating to plan sponsorship, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_15/CH_15_SEC200#CH_15_SEC200" target="_blank">15.321</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Mergers and spin-offs, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_15/CH_15_SEC162#CH_15_SEC162" target="_blank">15.731</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Minimum funding waiver submission to IRS, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_3B/CH_3B_SEC1967#CH_3B_SEC1967" target="_blank">3B.753</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Plan administration checklist, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_15/CH_15_SEC178#CH_15_SEC178" target="_blank">15.291</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Plan design checklist, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_15/CH_15_SEC177#CH_15_SEC177" target="_blank">15.263</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Plan termination checklist, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_15/CH_15_SEC1114#CH_15_SEC1114" target="_blank">15.801</a></b> (DC plans), <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_15/CH_15_SEC1145#CH_15_SEC1145" target="_blank">15.821</a></b> (DB plans)</p><p class="indent2">* QDROs, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_15/CH_15_SEC280#CH_15_SEC280" target="_blank">15.381</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* &#34;Red flags&#34; in plan design, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_15/CH_15_SEC287#CH_15_SEC287" target="_blank">15.391</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Rehired employee issues, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_15/CH_15_SEC326#CH_15_SEC326" target="_blank">15.421</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Reporting and disclosure requirements, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_15/CH_15_SEC328#CH_15_SEC328" target="_blank">15.441</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* SEPs compared to profit sharing plans, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_12/CH_12_SEC966#CH_12_SEC966" target="_blank">12.341</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Short plan year issues, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_15/CH_15_SEC200#CH_15_SEC200" target="_blank">15.351</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* SIMPLE-IRA plans compared to SARSEPS, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_12/CH_12_SEC1039#CH_12_SEC1039" target="_blank">12.331</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* SIMPLE-IRA plans compared to SIMPLE-401(k) plans, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_12/CH_12_SEC1038#CH_12_SEC1038" target="_blank">12.327</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* SIMPLE-IRAs, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_12/CH_12_SEC1022#CH_12_SEC1022" target="_blank">12.321</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Takeover plan issues, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_15/CH_15_SEC327#CH_15_SEC327" target="_blank">15.431</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* USERRA checklist, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_15/CH_15_SEC325#CH_15_SEC325" target="_blank">15.411</a></b></p><p class=""><b>CHURCHES AND CHURCH PLANS, see TAX-EXEMPT ORGANIZATIONS</b></p><p class=""><b>CIRCULAR 230, see INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE</b></p><p class=""><b>CIVIL PENALTIES, see DISCLOSURE TO PARTICIPANTS AND BENEFICIARIES, ENFORCEMENT OF ERISA</b></p></div><div id="CH_2_SEC001" style="text-align:left;" class="level1"><a name="CH_2_SEC001" id="CH_2_SEC001"></a><h2>CLAIMS PROCEDURE UNDER ERISA, see FIDUCIARY DUTY</h2></div><div id="CH_2_SEC001" style="text-align:left;" class="level1"><a name="CH_2_SEC001" id="CH_2_SEC001"></a><h2>CLASS EXEMPTIONS UNDER PROHIBITED TRANSACTION RULES, see PROHIBITED TRANSACTIONS</h2></div><div id="CH_2_SEC001" style="text-align:left;" class="level1"><a name="CH_2_SEC001" id="CH_2_SEC001"></a><h2>CLOSING AGREEMENTS WITH IRS, see PLAN DISQUALIFICATION</h2><p class=""><b>CODA, see SECTION 401(k) PLANS</b></p></div><div id="CH_2_SEC001" style="text-align:left;" class="level1"><a name="CH_2_SEC001" id="CH_2_SEC001"></a><h2>COLLECTIBLES</h2><p class="indent2">* Basis generated in account because of deemed distribution, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_7/CH_7_SEC145#CH_7_SEC145" target="_blank">7.42</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Deemed distribution if participant-directed account invests in collectibles, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_7/CH_7_SEC1476#CH_7_SEC1476" target="_blank">7.459</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Definition of collectibles, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_7/CH_7_SEC1471#CH_7_SEC1471" target="_blank">7.459</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* General trust investments not subject to deemed distribution treatment, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_7/CH_7_SEC1485#CH_7_SEC1485" target="_blank">7.461</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Pre-1982 acquisitions exempt, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_7/CH_7_SEC1479#CH_7_SEC1479" target="_blank">7.460</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Premature distribution penalty applies, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_7/CH_7_SEC1477#CH_7_SEC1477" target="_blank">7.459</a></b></p></div><div id="CH_2_SEC001" style="text-align:left;" class="level1"><a name="CH_2_SEC001" id="CH_2_SEC001"></a><h2>COLLECTIVE INVESTMENT FUNDS</h2><p class="indent2">* Special reporting requirements for plan assets held in,</p><p class="">see <b><a href="/browse-index/2014-erisa-outline-book/B001?indexKey=f#CH_3_SEC18">FORM 5500</a> SERIES</b></p><p class=""><b>COLLECTIVELY-BARGAINED EMPLOYEE</b></p><p class="indent2">* Definition of collectively-bargained employee, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_1A/CH_1A_SEC315#CH_1A_SEC315" target="_blank">1A.71</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Good faith bargaining on retirement benefits is required, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_1A/CH_1A_SEC317#CH_1A_SEC317" target="_blank">1A.71</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Professional individuals may not comprise more than 2% of the collective bargaining unit, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_1A/CH_1A_SEC319#CH_1A_SEC319" target="_blank">1A.71</a></b></p><p class=""><b>COLLECTIVELY-BARGAINED PLANS</b></p><p class="indent2">* Collectively-bargained employee, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_1A/CH_1A_SEC315#CH_1A_SEC315" target="_blank">1A.71</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Coverage rules applicable to,</p><p class="">see <b>COVERAGE TESTING</b></p><p class="indent2">* Definition of collectively-bargained plan, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_1A/CH_1A_SEC320#CH_1A_SEC320" target="_blank">1A.71</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Employee organization: definition of, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_1A/CH_1A_SEC816#CH_1A_SEC816" target="_blank">1A.212</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Multiemployer plans</p><p class="indent3">- Coverage testing issues for multiemployer plans, see <b>COVERAGE TESTING</b></p><p class="indent3">- Definition of multiemployer plan, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_1A/CH_1A_SEC1005#CH_1A_SEC1005" target="_blank">1A.414</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Enforcement of delinquent contributions,</p><p class="">see <b>ENFORCEMENT OF ERISA</b></p><p class="indent3">- Section 415 limits, application of to multiemployer plan,</p><p class="">see <b>SECTION 415 LIMITS</b></p><p class="indent3">- Taft-Hartley Act, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_1A/CH_1A_SEC1005#CH_1A_SEC1005" target="_blank">1A.414</a></b>, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_1B/CH_1B_SEC1075#CH_1B_SEC1075" target="_blank">1B.351</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Vesting schedules for multiemployer plans,</p><p class="">see <b>VESTING RULES</b></p><p class="indent2">* SIMPLE-IRA plans, coverage of union employees under,</p><p class="">see <b>SIMPLE PLANS</b></p><p class="indent2">* Top heavy rules, application of to collectively-bargained plans,</p><p class="">see <b>TOP HEAVY RULES</b></p><p class=""><b>COMMON LAW EMPLOYER-EMPLOYEE RELATIONSHIP</b></p><p class="indent2">* Independent contractor relationship, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_1A/CH_1A_SEC1005#CH_1A_SEC1005" target="_blank">1A.319</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Leased employee must be the common law employee of the leasing organization, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_1A/CH_1A_SEC1369#CH_1A_SEC1369" target="_blank">1A.359</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Professional Employer Organization (PEO) is not leasing organization if it is not the common law employer of worksite employees, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_1A/CH_1A_SEC1372#CH_1A_SEC1372" target="_blank">1A.360</a></b></p><p class=""><b>COMMON PAYMASTER, see COMPENSATION</b></p></div><div id="CH_2_SEC001" style="text-align:left;" class="level1"><a name="CH_2_SEC001" id="CH_2_SEC001"></a><h2>COMMON TRUST FUNDS</h2><p class="indent2">* Special reporting requirements for plan assets held in,</p><p class="">see <b><a href="/browse-index/2014-erisa-outline-book/B001?indexKey=f#CH_3_SEC18">FORM 5500</a> SERIES</b></p><p class=""><b>COMMONLY CONTROLLED TRADES OR BUSINESS, see RELATED ORGANIZATIONS (Controlled group of businesses)</b></p></div><div id="CH_2_SEC001" style="text-align:left;" class="level1"><a name="CH_2_SEC001" id="CH_2_SEC001"></a><h2>COMMUNITY PROPERTY INTERESTS</h2><p class="indent2">* Death benefit issues involving community property law,</p><p class="">see <b>DEATH BENEFITS</b></p><p class="indent2">* Definition of community property interest, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_1A/CH_1A_SEC323#CH_1A_SEC323" target="_blank">1A.72</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Excess retirement\ accumulations and distributions under IRC &#167;4980A calculations generally applied without regard to community property,</p><p class="">see <b>EXCESS RETIREMENT ACCUMULATIONS AND DISTRIBUTIONS</b></p><p class=""><i>Note: IRC &#167;4980A was repealed effective January 1, 1997.</i></p><p class="indent2">* Preemption of community property law,</p><p class="">see <b>ENFORCEMENT OF ERISA (Preemption)</b></p></div><div id="CH_2_SEC001" style="text-align:left;" class="level1"><a name="CH_2_SEC001" id="CH_2_SEC001"></a><h2>COMPENSATION</h2><p class="indent2">* Accrued compensation, <i>see <b>Section 415 compensation</b> below</i></p><p class="indent2">* Accrual of benefits, compensation definition used for,</p><p class="">see <b>ACCRUAL OF BENEFITS</b></p><p class="indent2">* Agency arrangements for payment of compensation, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_1A/CH_1A_SEC437#CH_1A_SEC437" target="_blank">1A.108</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Allocation of employer contributions, compensation definition used for,</p><p class="">see <b>ACCRUAL OF BENEFITS</b></p><p class="indent2">* Average compensation,</p><p class="">see <b>AVERAGE COMPENSATION</b></p><p class="indent2">* Base compensation,</p><p class="">see <b>PERMITTED DISPARITY</b></p><p class="indent2">* Change in the form of entity</p><p class="indent3">- Individual might have compensation and earned income in same year, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_1A/CH_1A_SEC703#CH_1A_SEC703" target="_blank">1A.183</a></b>, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_3B/CH_3B_SEC102#CH_3B_SEC102" target="_blank">3B.41</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Common paymaster for payment of compensation, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_1A/CH_1A_SEC438#CH_1A_SEC438" target="_blank">1A.108</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Compensation ratio test, <i>see <b>Section 414(s) compensation</b> below</i></p><p class="indent2">* Covered compensation,</p><p class="">see <b>PERMITTED DISPA