"CH_2_SEC001"></a><h2>COMPENSATION DOLLAR LIMIT</h2><p class="indent2">* Average compensation: application of dollar limit to calculation, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_3B/CH_3B_SEC026#CH_3B_SEC026" target="_blank">3B.09</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- May assume $200,000 limit was in effect in earlier years when determining accrued benefits in post-2001 plan years, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_3B/CH_3B_SEC028#CH_3B_SEC028" target="_blank">3B.10</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Compensation limit applied after compensation is reduced by elective deferrals, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_3B/CH_3B_SEC059#CH_3B_SEC059" target="_blank">3B.19</a></b>, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_11/CH_11_SEC291#CH_11_SEC291" target="_blank">11.86</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Deduction limits: effect of compensation dollar limit on calculation, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_7/CH_7_SEC1957#CH_7_SEC1957" target="_blank">7.634</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Defined benefit plans: application of compensation dollar limit, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_3B/CH_3B_SEC025#CH_3B_SEC025" target="_blank">3B.09</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Defined contribution plans: application of compensation dollar limit, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_3B/CH_3B_SEC011#CH_3B_SEC011" target="_blank">3B.3</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Elective deferrals: effect of compensation limit on deferral rate, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_3B/CH_3B_SEC044#CH_3B_SEC044" target="_blank">3B.14</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Application of plan limit on deferral election that is expressed as percentage of compensation, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_3B/CH_3B_SEC016#CH_3B_SEC016" target="_blank">3B.4</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* EPCRS correction method for failure to apply compensation dollar limit, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_15/CH_15_SEC848#CH_15_SEC848" target="_blank">15.694</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Governmental plans: exception from dollar limit for certain participants, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_3B/CH_3B_SEC065#CH_3B_SEC065" target="_blank">3B.21</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Indexed compensation dollar limits: table, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_17/CH_17_SEC007#CH_17_SEC007" target="_blank">17.23</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Matching contributions: effect of compensation limit, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_3B/CH_3B_SEC014#CH_3B_SEC014" target="_blank">3B.3</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Protected accrued benefits under defined benefit plan might be based on compensation in excess of dollar limit, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_3B/CH_3B_SEC036#CH_3B_SEC036" target="_blank">3B.13</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Self-employed individuals: effect of compensation dollar limit on earned income, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_3B/CH_3B_SEC087#CH_3B_SEC087" target="_blank">3B.37</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Short compensation periods: proration of compensation dollar limit, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_3B/CH_3B_SEC040#CH_3B_SEC040" target="_blank">3B.14</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Elective deferrals: special rule for deferrals calculated for payroll or other limited period, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_3B/CH_3B_SEC044#CH_3B_SEC044" target="_blank">3B.14</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Employee contributions: special rule for contributions calculated for payroll or other limited period, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_3B/CH_3B_SEC044#CH_3B_SEC044" target="_blank">3B.14</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Initial short plan year, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_3B/CH_3B_SEC046#CH_3B_SEC046" target="_blank">3B.15</a></b></p><p class="indent4">&#9670; Employer not in existence before the plan's effective date, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_3B/CH_3B_SEC049#CH_3B_SEC049" target="_blank">3B.15</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Limiting compensation to period of plan participation does not affect dollar limit, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_3B/CH_3B_SEC042#CH_3B_SEC042" target="_blank">3B.14</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Matching contributions: special rule for contributions calculated for payroll or other limited period, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_3B/CH_3B_SEC044#CH_3B_SEC044" target="_blank">3B.14</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Plan year in which plan terminates, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_3B/CH_3B_SEC050#CH_3B_SEC050" target="_blank">3B.16</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Short plan year, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_3B/CH_3B_SEC040#CH_3B_SEC040" target="_blank">3B.14</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* SIMPLE-IRA plans: application of dollar limit,</p><p class="">see <b>SIMPLE PLANS</b></p><p class="indent2">* SIMPLE-401(k) plans: application of dollar limit,</p><p class="">see <b>SIMPLE-401(k) PLANS</b></p><p class="indent2">* Termination of plan</p><p class="indent3">- Application of compensation dollar limit in plan year in which plan terminates, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_3B/CH_3B_SEC050#CH_3B_SEC050" target="_blank">3B.16</a></b></p><p class=""><b>COMPENSATION RATIO TEST, see COMPENSATION (Section 414(s) compensation)</b></p></div><div id="CH_2_SEC001" style="text-align:left;" class="level1"><a name="CH_2_SEC001" id="CH_2_SEC001"></a><h2>CONSENT REQUIREMENTS FOR CERTAIN DISTRIBUTIONS, see DISTRIBUTIONS</h2></div><div id="CH_2_SEC001" style="text-align:left;" class="level1"><a name="CH_2_SEC001" id="CH_2_SEC001"></a><h2>CONSTRUCTIVE RECEIPT</h2><p class="indent2">* Deferral of refunds under state disability program, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_1A/CH_1A_SEC292#CH_1A_SEC292" target="_blank">1A.63</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Discontinuance of defined benefit plan participant in exchange for enhanced defined contribution allocation, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_1A/CH_1A_SEC293#CH_1A_SEC293" target="_blank">1A.63</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Unused vacation: contribution to plan is not elective deferral because there is no cash election, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_1A/CH_1A_SEC289#CH_1A_SEC289" target="_blank">1A.62</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Also see <b>PTO PLANS</b></p><p class="indent2">* Use of unused sick leave to increase pension benefits did not result in taxable income because employee did not have cash election, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_1A/CH_1A_SEC291#CH_1A_SEC291" target="_blank">1A.63</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Also see <b>PTO PLANS</b></p></div><div id="CH_2_SEC001" style="text-align:left;" class="level1"><a name="CH_2_SEC001" id="CH_2_SEC001"></a><h2>CONSUMER FINANCIAL PROTECTION BUREAU</h2><p class="indent2">* Regulation Z: effect on certain retirement plan contributions made on behalf of loan originators, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_3A/CH_3A_SEC043#CH_3A_SEC043" target="_blank">3A.15</a></b></p><p class=""><b>CONTINGENT BENEFIT RULE, see SECTION 401(k) PLANS</b></p></div><div id="CH_2_SEC001" style="text-align:left;" class="level1"><a name="CH_2_SEC001" id="CH_2_SEC001"></a><h2>CONTRIBUTORY DEFINED BENEFIT PLANS, see NONDISCRIMINATION TESTING</h2></div><div id="CH_2_SEC001" style="text-align:left;" class="level1"><a name="CH_2_SEC001" id="CH_2_SEC001"></a><h2>CONTROLLED GROUP OF BUSINESSES, see ATTRIBUTION RULES, RELATED ORGANIZATIONS</h2></div><div id="CH_2_SEC001" style="text-align:left;" class="level1"><a name="CH_2_SEC001" id="CH_2_SEC001"></a><h2>CONVERSION OF PLAN INTO ANOTHER TYPE OF PLAN, see AMENDMENT OF PLAN</h2><p class=""><b>CORRECTIVE DISTRIBUTIONS, see ADP AND ACP TESTING, ELECTIVE DEFERRALS (Section 402(g) limit), SECTION 415 LIMITS</b></p></div><div id="CH_2_SEC001" style="text-align:left;" class="level1"><a name="CH_2_SEC001" id="CH_2_SEC001"></a><h2>COVERAGE TESTING</h2><p class="indent2">* 500-hour rule, <i>see <b>Excludable employees</b> below</i></p><p class="indent2">* Acquisition or disposition of related group members or business assets: special testing rule, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC345#CH_8_SEC345" target="_blank">8.133</a></b>, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC490#CH_8_SEC490" target="_blank">8.181</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Application of rule expanded by regulations, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC350#CH_8_SEC350" target="_blank">8.134</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Creation of new subsidiary in intra-company transaction not eligible for transition rule, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC357#CH_8_SEC357" target="_blank">8.136</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Determination letter no longer available to resolve proper application of transition rule, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC360#CH_8_SEC360" target="_blank">8.137</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Leasing of facility treated as similar transaction covered by transition rule, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC351#CH_8_SEC351" target="_blank">8.134</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Reliance on transition rule is optional, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC363#CH_8_SEC363" target="_blank">8.138</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Requirement that coverage is satisfied as of date of acquisition/disposition, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC361#CH_8_SEC361" target="_blank">8.137</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Significant change in coverage not permitted, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC352#CH_8_SEC352" target="_blank">8.134</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Spinoff of part of plan to another plan, pursuant to business acquisition, should not jeopardize reliance on transition rule, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC353#CH_8_SEC353" target="_blank">8.134</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Transition period ends prospectively if there is a significant change in coverage, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC354#CH_8_SEC354" target="_blank">8.135</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Aggregation of plans</p><p class="indent3">- Average benefits test, plan included in, <i>see <b>Average benefits test</b> below</i></p><p class="indent3">- Minimum participation test: aggregation of plans not permitted, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC466#CH_8_SEC466" target="_blank">8.175</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Permissive aggregation for ratio test or nondiscriminatory classification test, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC248#CH_8_SEC248" target="_blank">8.95</a></b></p><p class="indent4">&#9670; Benefiting group for the aggregated plans, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC251#CH_8_SEC251" target="_blank">8.95</a></b></p><p class="indent4">&#9670; Coverage testing group for the aggregated plans, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC250#CH_8_SEC250" target="_blank">8.96</a></b></p><p class="indent4">&#9670; Different age and service requirements for aggregated plans affects determination of excludable employees, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC273#CH_8_SEC273" target="_blank">8.104</a></b></p><p class="indent4">&#9670; ESOPs: special conditions must be satisfied in order to aggregate, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC255#CH_8_SEC255" target="_blank">8.102</a></b></p><p class="indent4">&#9670; Not available for plans subject to mandatory disaggregation, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC268#CH_8_SEC268" target="_blank">8.103</a></b></p><p class="indent4">&#9670; Otherwise excludable employee disaggregation under permissively aggregated plans, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC274#CH_8_SEC274" target="_blank">8.104</a></b></p><p class="indent4">&#9670; Same plan year required, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC271#CH_8_SEC271" target="_blank">8.104</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Section 403(b) may not be aggregated with qualified plan to help qualified plan pass coverage, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC247#CH_8_SEC247" target="_blank">8.90</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Amendment to cure coverage violation, <i>see <b>Failing coverage requirements</b> below</i></p><p class="indent2">* Average benefits test, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC139#CH_8_SEC139" target="_blank">8.51</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Average benefit percentage test, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC148#CH_8_SEC148" target="_blank">8.54</a></b></p><p class="indent4">&#9670; Aggregation of plans, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC171#CH_8_SEC171" target="_blank">8.60</a></b></p><p class="indent5">. . .DB and DC plans included in ratio: special rule, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC181#CH_8_SEC181" target="_blank">8.62</a></b></p><p class="indent5">. . .Different age and service requirements for plans included in average benefits ratio, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC186#CH_8_SEC186" target="_blank">8.64</a></b></p><p class="indent5">. . .Different plan years for plans aggregated under the average benefits test, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC182#CH_8_SEC182" target="_blank">8.63</a></b></p><p class="indent5">. . .ESOPs included with non-ESOPs in calculating ratio, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC177#CH_8_SEC177" target="_blank">8.61</a></b></p><p class="indent5">. . .Section 401(k) and 401(m) arrangements included in ratio with other plans (or other portions of plan), <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC172#CH_8_SEC172" target="_blank">8.60</a></b></p><p class="indent4">&#9670; Allocation rates for ABP purposes, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC156#CH_8_SEC156" target="_blank">8.55</a></b></p><p class="indent4">&#9670; Averaging period of two or three years permitted, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC166#CH_8_SEC166" target="_blank">8.58</a></b></p><p class="indent4">&#9670; Benefit percentage computations, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC155#CH_8_SEC155" target="_blank">8.55</a></b></p><p class="indent4">&#9670; Benefit rates for ABP purposes, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC157#CH_8_SEC157" target="_blank">8.55</a></b></p><p class="indent4">&#9670; Corrective distributions included in benefit percentages, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC167#CH_8_SEC167" target="_blank">8.58</a></b></p><p class="indent5">. . . Exclude excess contributions recharacterized as catch-up contributions, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC168#CH_8_SEC168" target="_blank">8.58</a></b><