erage, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC419#CH_8_SEC419" target="_blank">8.154</a></b></p><p class="indent2">* Minimum participation test (IRC &#167;401(a)(26))</p><p class="indent3">- 40% test requires at least 2 employees to benefit, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC449#CH_8_SEC449" target="_blank">8.171</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Acquisition or disposition of related group members, <i>see <b>Acquisition or disposition</b> above</i></p><p class="indent3">- Aggregation of plans not permitted, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC466#CH_8_SEC466" target="_blank">8.175</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Benefiting under the plan: how to determine who benefits under the plan for purposes of the minimum participation test, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC453#CH_8_SEC453" target="_blank">8.172</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Davis-Bacon plans: effect of defined contribution exemption from &#167;401(a)(26) testing, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC471#CH_8_SEC471" target="_blank">8.175</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Defined contribution plans exempt from &#167;401(a)(26) test, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC448#CH_8_SEC448" target="_blank">8.171</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Disaggregation rules under &#167;401(a)(26), <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC456#CH_8_SEC456" target="_blank">8.173</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Excise tax on reversions: exemption for certain terminations necessitated by IRC &#167;401(a)(26), <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_7/CH_7_SEC2371#CH_7_SEC2371" target="_blank">7.775</a></b>, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC496#CH_8_SEC496" target="_blank">8.183</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Excludable employees for purposes of the 40% test, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC451#CH_8_SEC451" target="_blank">8.172</a></b></p><p class="indent3">- Flexibility for defined contribution plan designs, <b><a href="/FullText/B001/CH_8/CH_8_SEC470#CH_8_SEC470" target="_blank">8.175</a></b></p><p cla